Description: Beautiful 4 bedroom, 2 bath, 1750 square foot 1998 Silvercrest Westwood home. [Serial Number(s): 17306271A, 1730271B] This model originally purchased through Advantage Homes was a 5 bedroom model and if you desire to add the 5th bedroom, you can put up one wall, which will not require a permit. Maximum occupancy is 9, with addition of 5th bedroom, 11. Features include a covered front porch, over-sized lot with mature lilac bushes, double pane windows, tandem parking for 2+ car under carport. The open concept living area with vaulted ceilings includes privacy sheers on the windows, vaulted ceilings and dining / multimedia area. The kitchen features new marble countertops and island, new wood cabinets, walk in pantry, upgraded garbage disposal and recessed LED lighting. A 4 speed Wall Range Hood over the gas stove for the Master Chef. The master suite includes a privacy blinds, a walk in closet, dual sinks with marble counter tops, walk-in shower & garden tub. Beautiful second bathroom with tub & shower combo and marble countertop. New door locks, and LED porch lights and LED lighting throughout home. Utility room has a full-sized washer and dryer (included) cabinetry, and exterior carport door. Vinyl Plank Flooring throughout the entire home. This home has been remodeled inside and outside. New roof and gutters in July 2019 and the home was re-leveled and inspections passed for furnace, plumbling, drains, gas and electric lines. This home is perfect for all ages as there are no age restrictions in Mary Manor Park. Enjoy the heated pool and spa with nearby restroom, a clubhouse and an area for car washing. Unlike other parks in Sunnyvale there is plenty of visitor parking. There is an area for RV/vehicle storage that park tenants can rent. AGENTS with pre-approved or cash buyers welcome! PARK: Mgmt. approval by Mary Manor is required before offers considered. Space rent payable to Mary Manor: $1,500.00 per month (which is 700 less than some other parks in Sunnyvale) RESIDENCY: Owners can rent out rooms but cannot rent out the entire house. As stated in the Park Rules and Regulation, Rule #15: No subletting, subleasing, or renting of homes or homesites is allowed. Mary Manor Estates is for owner-occupied homes. At all times, at least ONE full-time park-approved Resident must be listed as the Registered Owner of the home occupied, according to HCD or County tax records. Property Taxes due December and April: $900 / year The location is ideal for anyone who works in the Peninsula or the Santa Clara Valley. TRANSIT: Cal Train Station is 1 mile east on Evelyn. The Whisman Light Rail Station is 1.7 miles west. The VTA Bus Stop is one block north on Central Expressway / N. Mary Avenue. Major roads: Central Expressway is one block from Park. It will take you north right into the heart of Palo Alto or south ending at San Jose International Airport. Distance to Freeways: 101 ? 4 miles, 237 ? 2 miles, 85 ? 2 miles, 280 is about 10 minutes depending on route taken. The home is located between downtown Sunnyvale and historic downtown Mountain View which both have farmers markets on the weekends. Restaurants, shopping, entertainment all within a short drive. SCHOOL Districts: Sunnyvale School District, Fremont Union High School District Vargas Elementary School, 1054 Carson Drive, Sunnyvale Grades K-5 0.3 mi Sunnyvale Middle School, 1080 Mango Ave, Sunnyvale Grades 6-8 1.7 mi Homestead High School, 21370 Homestead Rd, Cupertino Grades 9-12 3.3 miRead more

Description: A magnificent custom home situated on a desirable court in the Weibel area speaks to those who want just that; the very best. Situated on over a 1/2 Acre lot, this 4266 square foot home has it all, from its updated gourmet kitchen , palatial master and updated designer baths , its majestic park like rear yard , and its fantastic views. This home's grand curb appeal is highlighted by its contemporary design which accent its exterior both front and back. Step inside this remodeled beauty and one can only appreciate its uplifting feel and light and extensive updates throughout its fantastic floor plan. Updated gourmet kitchen offers rich custom cabinetry, granite slab counters including a large granite island, new stainless gas stove , 20 foot stainless French door refrigerator, convection oven with built-in microwave, stainless dishwasher , wine cooler, to enhance your cooking and entertaining needs along with a pantry. Step up formal dining room allows for large gatherings and formal settings for family events or holiday. Walk up to the large master suite complete with a gracious walk-in closet and you have it all accompanied by a stunning remodeled designer master bathroom. It offers high quality cabinetry, his and her vanities with marble counters, underneath and above accent lighting to set the mood, frameless shower featuring porcelain tile, and a soaker tub adjacent to your sun filled bay windows. Take in a sun-filled afternoon in the upstairs sunroom and read a book or just relax. All other bedrooms are an excellent size and the downstairs guest room is ideal for overnight visitors or family members! Take advantage of the game room or make it a media room as it has multi-purpose use for your future needs! It could even be converted to a guest quarters(buyer to verify) Spacious family room offers high ceilings, accent lighting , new ceiling fan and large picture windows allowing for an abundance of natural light. It is also wired for surround sound, features a gas starter fireplace, and has sliding doors that lead you to your meticulously landscaped rear yard featuring a waterfall ,verdant lawns, a putting green and even your own sand trap! If you love to golf , this could be your playground! Not to mention , a park like setting with mature trees giving you peace and solace after that long day at work. Description: Located in Treasure Isle on a charming cul-de-sac, this stately five-bedroom, two and one half-bath home offers timeless appeal. Downstairs the foyer opens onto a formal living room and the spacious dining room perfect for entertaining. The lower level of the home wraps around to the dining room and kitchen with breakfast nook. The family room showcases a full bar and beautiful views of the water. The solarium is ideal for your morning cup of coffee while you watch the sun rise. The large two car garage, with laundry and built in cabinets, may be accessed from the family room. Upstairs features four bedrooms and the expansive master suite. The master bedroom overlooks the water and backyard, and shares a deck with the adjacent bedroom. The home offers sweeping views of the water and private access to Erckenbrack Park. The lagoon wraps around much of this 15,884 square foot lot and provides a stunning setting for the rare, and sizable backyard.Read more

Description: Beautiful, bright, spacious & well maintained Waterfront Townhouse from Harbor Town community. Enjoy the warmness/sunshine while youre sitting at home. Description: The legendary Gold Coast of Pacific Heights is an elite enclave on Outer Broadway known for its majestic homes, notable residents and unsurpassed views. Here, on a coveted corner lot set high above the city and the bay, this imposing 11,600± sq.ft. mansion is the foremost offering on the market in San Francisco, presenting a rare opportunity to own a custom-built residence in a world-class location with world-class views. Impressively engineered of concrete and steel and completed circa 2004, it displays quality construction, craftsmanship and refinement. The eminently comfortable home has six bedrooms--five en suite--seven full baths, and two half baths. Floors are clad in walnut, raw limestone and marble. High-ceilinged public spaces are airy, open, and ideal for entertaining on any scale. The centerpiece of the home is a spectacular serpentine staircase with ornate railings crafted by Italian artisans. The property features interior design by both Ken Fulk and Eric Cohler, elevator access to four levels, a secondary back staircase, smart home technology, radiant heating, two working fireplaces, hand-plastered walls, mahogany doors and windows, a four-car garage with an EV charging station, and abundant storage. A formal entry facing Broadway begins with a grand portrait hall with 20-foot ceilings, marble floors, and a dramatic double staircase. An extensive wine cellar with tasting area is also located on this level. The second level is comprised of a study and two bedrooms, including a two-room guest suite. On the third level is a vibrant, open library with mahogany-paneled walls, coffered ceilings, built-in bookcases, a bay window with a lovely view, and a decorative fireplace with a custom glass mosaic. The handsome pub and billiards room has an antique bar reclaimed from a British tavern. Completing this level are an elegant guest suite with quilted leather walls, a private fitness room, and a large laundry room with a pet bathing station. The fourth floor is the heart of the home. Filled with glorious volume and light, the main public spaces feature 14 sets of French doors and include a living and dining salon with bay views and glowing cerulean walls of burnished enamel; a separate sitting area; and a magnificent, open-plan great room encompassing the kitchen, a casual dining space with built-in banquette, and a family room with a wall of bookshelves. Four sets of French doors give way to a protected, sunny south terrace and artificial-turf lawn. Chefs and entertainers will appreciate the kitchen, which features an island; custom mahogany cabinetry; Italian milk glass countertops; a Thermador range with a copper hood; pairs of Sub-Zero refrigerators, dishwashers, ovens, and sinks; a built- in desk; and a butler's pantry with a third Sub-Zero. Two thoughtful power rooms conclude this level. Here also is found a less formal, rear entrance to the home via the landscaped terrace. On the uppermost level are two charming family bedroom suites--one with its own south terrace--and a lavish master suite boasting a classically detailed bath with a soaking tub; an expansive, impeccably appointed walk-in closet and dressing area; and a fireplace. The pièce de résistance is the master bedroom's walkout terrace, which includes a spa. Here, unparalleled, panoramic views unfold from the Golden Gate Bridge and the Marin Headlands, across San Francisco Bay, and all the way to the Oakland Hills, showcasing such landmarks as the Palace of Fine Arts, Alcatraz and Angel Island. Also known as Billionaire's Row, these three tranquil blocks offer respite from busy city life yet are just blocks from the boutiques, restaurants and shops of fashionable Sacramento Street. Nearby are Julius Kahn Playground as well as the Presidio - a national park and historic district - which offers the Presidio Golf Course, miles of trails, picnic areas, museums, restaurants, Crissy Field, and Baker Beach.Read more

Description: Originally built in 1906 by the renowned father and son architect team of Newsom & Newsom, this Classic Revival Residence located on one of the premier blocks of Pacific Heights recently experienced a resurgence of glowing accolades. The Mack Mansion of yesteryear was artfully reimagined for a contemporary aesthete, while respectfully paying homage to its rich heritage. Juxtaposed with the modern designer decor, classic architectural details still abound from the grand escalier crafted in dark wood with wrought-iron balusters to the immediately recognizable circular temple-style portico white marble front entrance. Description: This expansive Spanish-Revival residence, designed by Charles Whittlesey in 1908, has been substantially and thoughtfully renovated into a warm, light-filled home with beautiful scale. Spanning approximately 5,900 square feet, this 5 bedroom, 5 and a half bath Presidio Heights home offers a sophisticated floor plan, indoor-outdoor living and Golden Gate Bridge views. On the main level, your eyes are drawn to the graceful wood beams accenting the living and dining rooms. Spanning the front of the home, the generous living area has multiple seating areas and a fireplace inviting cozy conversation. The dining room can accommodate a large gathering or an intimate dinner party, and the curved nook opens to the spacious patio. One floor above and connected by a graceful staircase, the master retreat commands your attention. Comprising a spacious bedroom, separate sitting area, spa-like bath, and large walk-in closet, this suite also has a secluded hot tub on the connected deck. Also on this level is another bedroom with ensuite bath, walk-in closet and built-in desk. A laundry room with drying closet is conveniently located on this floor. On the uppermost level, discover stunning Golden Gate bridge views from the well-appointed office, as well as two generously-sized bedrooms and two spacious baths. A large skylight over the stairwell fills the space with light. An expansive South-facing deck on this level also has bay and bridge views, and offers a relaxing outdoor sanctuary. The generous space on the lower level offers a myriad of possibilities: media lounge, fitness area, music room, guest space. Equipped with a decorative fireplace and multiple windows, this room is waiting for your personalization. The impressive, resort-like outdoor space boasts multiple seating areas, putting green and basketball hoop, a thriving vegetable garden and mature plantings. Large sliding doors connect the space directly to the kitchen for ease of entertaining. Completing the home is an elevator and spacious two-car garage with abundant storage. 3445 Washington Street is located on a highly-sought after block of Presidio Heights, just minutes from The Presidio, Presidio Heights Playground and the shops and restaurants of Sacramento Street and Laurel Village. Summary: * Beautifully renovated home with original architectural detail and glorious natural light * 5 bedrooms, 5 full baths, 1 half bath, 2 offices and a playroom/studio * Approximately 5,887 square feet of living space (per tax records); Lot size: 40x125 * Warm hardwood floors, gracious archways and an architectural staircase throughout * Large-scale living room with fireplace and custom shelving * Spacious formal dining room with adjacent sitting area * Remodeled kitchen with center island, gleaming copper hood and two sinks * Appliances include Wolf range and double oven, Subzero refrigerator/freezer, and two Miele dishwashers. * Casual dining space adjacent to the kitchen, wine storage and built-in bench seating * Large slide-away doors open directly to the outdoor terrace * Upstairs master retreat has an expansive walk-in closet, spa like-bathroom, sitting/yoga room and secluded deck with hot tub * Additional upstairs rooms include a view playroom/studio, a bedroom with built in desk, walk-in closet and en-suite bath and a laundry room with drying closet * Top level has a panoramic view office, two spacious bedrooms, 2 full baths and a large south-facing deck with bridge views * Elevator * Multiple view balconies * 2 car tandem garage with storage * Terraced outdoor space with putting green, basketball hoop and multiple seating areasRead more

Description: Discover this rare opportunity in the beautiful Ingleside Terraces! Parking abounds with a detached side-by-side two-car garage and long driveway, although you can also leave your cars behind with Ocean Ave shops and restaurants, Muni, and BART all in easy reach. Description: Scenic view home in the heart of the Marina, eschewing understated elegance throughout, is steps away from the Palace of Fine Arts, St. Francis Yacht Club, Marina Green and Crissy Field. Situated on one of the most exclusive blocks in San Francisco, this home was built in 1929 and features classic doorways as well as extensive crown moldings. Dramatic picture windows showcase awe-inspiring vistas overlooking San Francisco Bay, including magnificent sailboats and gigantic ships coasting from around the world. The mature landscaped front yard complete with olive trees leads to a sinuous exterior stairway, beckoning you through an arched front door and into a gracious foyer with its impressive open staircase. MAIN LEVEL Light-filled and welcoming, the main level of this home delights with its charming character and well-thought-out floor plan. The magnificent formal living room with its floor to ceiling bay windows has custom stained-glass panes on either side of the stately fireplace. An oversized picture window boasts incredible views of the Marina Green and beyond, across the bay and to Sausalito. A grand formal dining room features crown molding and a pocket door leading into the kitchen with sumptuous views of the nearby harbor. An updated chef's kitchen includes custom concrete countertops, greenhouse windows plus Wolf, Subzero, and Gaggineau appliances. The adjoining spacious breakfast room opens to a deck with bay views and plenty of space for a potted herb garden. The partially enclosed wrap around deck extends the living space outdoors and is perfect for entertaining. Additional cabinets with a wine refrigerator adjoin the large and well located laundry room with plenty of storage. A lovely tiled bathroom with shower and Toto commode completes the main level. UPPER LEVEL A gracious top floor landing is filled with natural light emanating through oversized casement windows. The spacious master bedroom with its sitting area is bathed in afternoon sunshine. Closets include a built in dressing table. The sliding glass door opens to "Juliet's balcony" with stunning views of the Marina Green, Palace of Fine Art and glimpses of the beach, bay and beyond to Sausalito. The updated split tiled hall bathroom has a step-up jetted bathtub, walk-in shower and Toto commode. There are three additional large bedrooms which feature crown molding and multiple windows, further brightening the living space. A tiled bathroom with shower is located between two of the bedrooms. These bedrooms offer views of the Marina Green, St. Francis Yacht Club and Alcatraz. LOWER LEVEL Separate guest/au pair quarters may be accessed from the garage or private exterior entry. This area includes a spacious living room with a large river stone fireplace and built-in desk with bookshelves, eat-in tiled kitchen including dishwasher, spacious bedroom and step-down tiled bathroom with shower over tub. The private, low maintenance garden with mature landscaping and brick patio is accessed through the kitchen's dutch door or alternatively through a north facing walkway. There is a dedicated washer and dryer for these quarters. A four-car garage with ample storage and workshop potential completes this level.Read more

Description: Looking for that spacious, move-in ready home for you and yours? Look no further as we have the place for you! Stroll past the fantastic curb appeal on this cute corner lot and walk into your new home! Be immediately greeted by the stone tile guiding you into the updated kitchen. Lots of hardwood cabinets, granite counters and tiled backsplash give a luxury aesthetic while the center island provides tons of prep space. A gas range, the preference of any chef, stands ready to help create your favorite meals! Also, the connected dining room will provide great interaction with your loved ones as you cook. Around the corner, locate the living room. Expansive space and the hardwood floors throughout contribute to the comfortable tranquility in this room. Connecting is the additional family room. Bright lighting, plantation shutters and vaulted ceilings allow this room the ability to entertain! Down the hall, find the beds and baths. All the standard bedrooms possess more hardwoods, large closets and good space. They are supported by the bath boasting new laminates, full tub and dual vanities. Finally, step into your master oasis! Imagine waking in natural light prior to entering your private en-suite bath, an ideal way to calmly prepare for the day! Out back, your private back yard compliments the big front yard. Framed by quality wood fencing, this area comes complete with your own storage shed. Visualize making the large patio into your own outdoor living space. Envision guests laughing as you barbecue in the sunshine, truly a great recipe for tremendous memories! All these great features are bolstered by the outstanding location! Great commuter access will be yours due to proximity to Hwys 880 and 84, in addition to the BART station just a couple minutes away. Short walks connect you to shopping, schools, restaurants and recreation in all directions. This home will raise your quality of life!Read more

Description: What I love about this homeOne of the things she discovered early about Midtown was its convenient location. "I pretty much knew that I could walk pretty much everywhere," she said. The parks are another perk of the neighborhood. "The parks are so beautiful," she said. The family often spends time at nearby Hoover and Bowden parks, a contrast to her childhood neighborhood in Orange County, where there was only one "big giant park" to which her mother had to drive her. Midtown, named because it is roughly in the middle of Palo Alto, sits between Oregon Expressway and Loma Verde Avenue, and West Bayshore Road and Alma Street. With about 5,000 families living in a mix of homes from Eichler to Craftsman style, the neighborhood has its own shopping district, including a grocery store. "I feel like all of our neighbors are neighborly," Lee said, often comparing notes on things like smelling a skunk in their yards, or how family members are doing after catching the flu. Unlike Lee, Webster Street resident LeAnn Baum found Midtown accidentally when she and her husband moved from San Francisco. "While we love Midtown, we didn't choose our house because it's in Midtown. It was luck," said Baum, who has two children, 5 and 6 years old. "We love the low-key atmosphere of Midtown as compared to the busier downtown area of Palo Alto. We appreciate being off the beaten path," she said. "Midtown has a nice balance of nice parks, shops, restaurants and other amenities."Read more
